 1→//axhob_operation
 2→{rbtgo_ark_conjure}
 3→
 4→NOTE: This operation conjures an
 5→{rbtga_ark}
 6→in
 7→{rbtgi_repository}
 8→by building a container image from a vessel specification and assembling build provenance metadata. The
 9→{rbtr_director}
10→performs the build via
11→{gcb_service}.
12→
13→NOTE: This is the ark-level view of the build operation. For detailed build procedure steps, see
14→{rbtgo_trigger_build}.
15→
16→The conjure operation:
17→
18→//axhop_parameter_from_type
19→{rbtgr_vessel_dir}
20→. *Validate Input Parameters*:
21→.. {rbbc_require}
22→vessel directory provided as first argument
23→.. {rbbc_require}
24→vessel contains conjuring configuration (RBRV_CONJURE_DOCKERFILE, RBRV_CONJURE_BLDCONTEXT)
25→
26→//axhos_step
27→. *Execute Build*:
28→.. Delegate to
29→{rbtgo_trigger_build}
30→which dispatches via the vessel's
31→{rbtgr_vessel_trigger}
32→.. All build parameters baked in
33→{rbtgr_build_json}
34→— zero custom substitution overrides
35→.. Waits for build completion
36→.. On success, both
37→{rbtga_ark_image}
38→and
39→{rbtga_ark_about}
40→artifacts are created with shared
41→{rbtga_consecration}
42→.. {rbtgr_provenance}
43→is auto-generated by Google as a signed attestation on the built image
44→
45→//axhoo_output_of_type
46→{rbtga_ark}
47→. *Display Results*:
48→.. {rbbc_show}
49→vessel image built with consecration tag
50→
51→//axhoc_completion
52→Successful execution creates a complete
53→{rbtga_ark}
54→with both image and about artifacts sharing the same
55→{rbtga_consecration}.
